A MANHUNT was launched after six houses were torched in the evening of Tuesday, 8 June, in Ravele village in Tshilwavhusiku, Limpopo. Police spokesperson Brigadier Motlafela Mojapelo said the incident could be linked to acts of mob justice. “Preliminary police investigations revealed that this incident of mob justice could be linked to the murders previously committed in the area. But the suspects in these cases have already been arrested. ALSO READ: WOMAN 'KILLS' HUSBAND, COOKS HIS 4-5! Provincial police Commissioner Lieutenant-General Thembi Hadebe has strongly condemned incidents of mob justice, and directed the police to hunt down the suspects and bring them to book,” Mojapelo added.